    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sorted 1999 Porsche 911 Carrera, featuring the 3.4L naturally aspirated flat-six M96 powerplant and a 6-speed Getrag manual transaxle. This example is an enthusiast-spec driver, benefiting from a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a recent RMS replacement. The suspension geometry remains precise thanks to updated control arms and Bilstein B6 dampers, preserving the communicative feedback of the hydraulic steering rack. The engine pulls strongly through the rev range with a linear power band and no signs of bore scoring. While the exterior shows minor stone chips consistent with spirited use, the chassis integrity and drivetrain performance are excellent. Ideal for the purist seeking a visceral, analog driving experience.",
